  "body": "## Issue\r\n\r\nUnder certain conditions, the elements of the `abi` member of the Truffle artifact will be missing their `signature` element.  This can occur even for concrete contracts (not just interfaces and abstract contracts).  (And, really, there's no reason not to include them even for contracts that aren't concrete.)\r\n\r\n(Note that @gnidan suggests that actually the `signature` element should *always* be missing, but I'm filing this anyway for completeness.)\r\n\r\n## Steps to Reproduce\r\n\r\nCompile a Truffle project with the following contract file:\r\n\r\n```\r\npragma solidity ^0.5.0;\r\n\r\ncontract TestAbstract {\r\n  function doThingA() public;\r\n}\r\n\r\ncontract TestConcrete is TestAbstract {\r\n\r\n  function doThingA() public {\r\n  }\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\n## Expected Behavior\r\n\r\nThe artifact for `TestConcrete` should have signatures.  (And, IMO, as mentioned above, the artifact for `TestAbstract` should too, even though I'm guessing their omission was deliberate.)\r\n\r\n## Actual Results\r\n\r\nThe artfact for `TestConcrete` (as well as the artifact for `TestAbstract`) did not have signatures.",
